import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='population', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.legend(title='Population by State', loc='upper right', labels=data['state'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='population', y='engineers', hue='state', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of engineers and the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='hurricanes', data=data, marker='o', ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hurricanes across the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Hurricanes'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
